sual in the United States. Hyundai’s Metaplant in Georgia produces the Ioniq 5 alongside the Ioniq 9 EV. The Kona Electric, however, is exported from South Korea to various markets, including the United States and Europe.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Hyundai Ioniq 9\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"6800\" height=\"3825\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MjI0/large-64254-2026ioniq9-887224.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eIn late March, Hyundai announced a $21 billion investment in the United States. Those funds will go towards opening a new steel plant, increasing United States production capacity, and expanding partnerships with United States companies.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003csection\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2026 Hyundai Palisade XRT PRO\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 24px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwNDM5/Large-65388-2026PalisadeICEXRTPRO.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"hyundai-is-offering-incentives-to-spur-sales\"\u003eHyundai is offering incentives to spur sales\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eCooling EV sales are largely a result of countries changing their policies towards EV adoption. The United States, Canada, and several European countries, including Germany, recently made changes to their subsidy programs that had helped drive EV sales. That’s not to mention the looming threat of tariffs and EV policy changes from the Trump administration.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Hyundai Ioniq 6\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8256\" height=\"5504\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg4MjQ5/large-61967-2025ioniq6limited-888249.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eIn response to sluggish EV sales, Hyundai has turned to zero-interest financing deals in North America and down payment assistance in several European countries. Unfortunately, those incentives haven’t proved as fruitful as the South Korean automaker had hoped.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eEarlier this month, Hyundai stated it would keep the sticker prices on its current models steady until June 2nd. The program is an effort to ease consumer concerns regarding vehicle prices amid uncertainty caused by tariffs. \u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Hyundai Ioniq 5\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"6000\" height=\"4000\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEwNTY2NTYzOTg2Njc5NjMz/2025-hyundai-ioniq-5-114759.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eHyundai isn’t the only automaker looking to incentivize new vehicle sales. \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/ford/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eFord\u003c/a\u003e plans to offer employee pricing to all consumers through June 2nd and Stellantis is currently offering employee pricing or cash incentives through April 30th.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eHyundai is coming off a fantastic year in the United States, but that doesn’t seem to be the case in its domestic market. The Korean automaker’s production was put on hold in February due to domestic sales, but now, slowing sales have spread to its foreign markets as well. Government policies regarding EVs have been uncertain and, in some cases, erratic, which has led to a cooling market. With eight months left to go in 2025, EVs still have a chance to bounce back. That said, with Tesla’s sales in a freefall, Hyundai has an opportunity to carve out more market share for itself – if the automaker can figure out how to further incentivize consumers.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003csection\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 24px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkyMTA5/20231130_INFINITI_1-2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
